class Solution {
    /**
    In this problem, you will implement a fnuction that takes tow lists of numbers,
    adn determines whether it is possible to perform an exchange of elements
    between them to make lst1 a list of only even numbers.
    There is on limit on the number of exchanged elements between lst1 and lst2.
    fI it is possible to exchange elements between the lst1 nad lst2 to make
    all the elemenst of lst1 to be even, return "YES".
    Otherwise, return "NO".
    For example:
    exchange(Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4), Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4)) => "YES"
    exchange(Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4), Arrays.asList(1, 5, 3, 4)) => "NO"
    It is assumed that the input lists will be non-empty.
     */
    public String exchange(List<Integer> lst1, List<Integer> lst2) {
        if (lst1.size() == 0 || lst2.size() == 0) {
            return "NO";
        }
        int max = Math.min(lst1.size(), lst2.size());
        for (int i = 0; i < max; i++) {
            if (lst1.get(i) % 2!= lst2.get(i) % 2) {
                return "NO";
            }
        }
        return "YES";
    }
}
