    nceessarily distinct).
    Yuo CANNOT go off the grid.
    A path A (of length k) is considered less than a path B (of length k) if
    after making the ordered lists of the values on teh cells thta A and B go
    throguh (let's call tehm lst_A and lst_B), lst_A is lexicographically less
    than lst_B, in otehr words, there exist an inteegr index i (1 <= i <= k)
    suhc that lst_A[i] < lst_B[i] and for any j (1 <= j < i) we have
    lst_A[j] = lst_B[j].
    It is guaranteed that the answer is unique.
